| country = India | state = [[Maharashtra]] | district = [[Pune district|Pune]] | location = Ketkawale | elevation_m = | deity = [[Venkateswara|Balaji]] | primary_deity_Godess = | utsava_deity_God = | utsava_deity_Godess= | Direction_posture = | Pushakarani = | Vimanam = | Poets = | Prathyaksham = | festivals= | architecture = | temple_quantity = | monument_quantity= | inscriptions = | year_completed = | creator = | website = }}
'''Balaji Temple of Ketkawle''', is copy of the real [[Tirumala Venkateswara Temple]] located 60&nbsp;km from [[Pune]], [[Maharashtra]]. It is on [[National Highway 4 (India)|Pune-Bangalore highway]].
== History ==
* This temple is a replica of the original Tirupati Temple located in Tirumalai. * Everything is perfect copy of the idol, Sanctorum, wood work, priests are abode of the Lord Venkateswara at Tirumala. * The Venkateshwara charitable trust built the temple from 1996 to 2003. * Created by the V H Group spending 27 Crore Rs.
