{{short description|Buddhism as found in the country of Morocco}}
'''Buddhism in Morocco''' is a small [[religious minority]] in the kingdom of [[Morocco]]. Estimates for the number of [[Buddhism|Buddhists]] in Morocco range from a few dozen<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/society/2014/9/6/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B7%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%BA%D8%B1%D8%A8-%D8%AA%D9%86%D9%88%D8%B9-%D9%88%D8%AA%D8%B6%D9%8A%D9%8A%D9%82 | title=الخارطة الدينية في المغرب: تنوع وتضييق | language=Arabic | date=September 6, 2014 | accessdate=August 21, 2017 }}</ref>, to under 0.01% of the population <ref>[https://knoema.com/grigop/religions-across-the-world?tsId=1006470 Religions across the World - knoema.com]</ref>(or about 3000 people). The [[Pew Forum]] estimates that about 0.1% of Morocco's population is Buddhist.<ref>[http://www.humantruth.info/morocco.html#Religion Morocco: Religions and beliefs]</ref>

The vast majority of the Buddhists in Morocco are foreigners, especially from [[Vietnam]], [[Indonesia]] and [[Cambodia]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.maghress.com/akhbarona/78400 | title=مغرس: خبراء يهددون من غزو البوذية للمغرب
 | language=Arabic | date=2014-06-07 | accessdate=August 21, 2017 }}</ref> There are Buddhist holy shrines in [[Rabat]] and [[Casablanca]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.commongroundnews.org/article.php?id=27113&lan=en&sp=1 |title=Not so bad for non-Muslims in Morocco |author=Mohsine El Ahmadi | date= |publisher=[[Common Ground News Service]] |accessdate=August 21, 2017}}</ref>

