{{Infobox organization |name= Covenant of Unitarian Universalist Pagans |image=Cuupslogo.png |size= |caption= |abbreviation= CUUPS |formation= 1985 |extinction= |type= [[Religious organization]] |purpose= Serve Unitarian Universalist community who identify with [[Paganism]] or [[Modern paganism|Neopaganism]] |headquarters=[[Hurst, Texas|Hurst]], [[Texas]], US |location= United States |affiliations= |membership= |language= |leader_title=President |leader_name=Amy Beltaine |leader_title2=Executive Director |leader_name2=David Pollard |key_people= |num_staff= |budget= |website= {{official URL}} }}
The '''Covenant of Unitarian Universalist Pagans''' ('''CUUPS''') is an association of [[Unitarian Universalism|Unitarian Universalists]] who identify with the precepts of [[Paganism|classical]] or [[contemporary Paganism]]: celebrating the sacred circle of life and guiding people to live in harmony with the rhythms of nature. CUUPS members foster the development of "liturgical materials based on earth- and nature-centered religious and spiritual perspectives" as well as encourage "greater use of music, dance, visual arts, poetry, story, and creative ritual in Unitarian Universalist worship and celebration."<ref>[http://www.cuups.org/about/vision.html CUUPS: Vision Statement]</ref>
==History== CUUPS was formed at the 1985 [[Unitarian Universalist Association#General Assembly|UUA General Assembly]] and incorporated as a not for profit organization in 1997. It was an Independent Affiliate of the [[Unitarian Universalist Association]] until 2007,<ref>{{cite book | last = Adler | first = Margot | authorlink = | title = Drawing Down the Moon: Witches, Druids, Goddess-Worshippers, and Other Pagans in America Today | edition = revised | publisher = [[Penguin Books]] | year = 2006 | page = 435 | isbn = 0-14-019536-X}}</ref> then a Related Organization,<ref>{{Cite web | title = UUA: Related Organizations, Theology/Academic Groups | publisher = Unitarian Universalist Association of Congregations | date = 13 May 2010 | url = http://www.uua.org/aboutus/organizations/search.php?category=11669 | accessdate = 3 Jan 2011 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20100613080341/http://uua.org/aboutus/organizations/search.php?category=11669 | archivedate = 13 June 2010 | df = }}</ref> and as of 2015 a Covenanting Community<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.uua.org/growth/covenanting|title=Covenanting Communities|date=2016-07-25|work=UUA.org|access-date=2017-07-30|language=en}}</ref> of the UUA. There are now nearly 70 chapters of CUUPS.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cuups.org/chapters/index.html|title=CUUPS Chapters|website=www.cuups.org|access-date=2017-04-20}}</ref>
==Purpose== CUUPS works to enrich and strengthen the [[religious pluralism]] of Unitarian Universalism; promote the study and practice of contemporary Pagan, Earth-, and nature-centered spirituality; enable networking among pagan-identified Unitarian Universalists; develop educational/liturgical materials on Pagan spirituality for Unitarian Universalist congregations; encourage theological inquiry into the contemporary Pagan resurgence; promote inter-religious dialog; and work for the healing of the Earth. While not directly related to Wicca or other explicit Pagan paths, it does embrace them within its ministerial tradition.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Puckett|first=Robert|date=2009-01-26|title=Re-enchanting the world: A weberian analysis of wiccan charisma|url=http://booksandjournals.brillonline.com/content/books/10.1163/ej.9789004163737.i-650.35|pages=121–152|doi=10.1163/ej.9789004163737.i-650.35}}</ref> Members and friends receive the online CUUPS Bulletin, which reports continental and local chapter activities and explores contemporary Paganism.<ref>[http://www.cuups.org/ Covenant of Unitarian Universalist Pagans, Inc.], official web site</ref>
The organization maintains ties to the UK-based [[Unitarian Earth Spirit Network]], which serves a similar role of representing contemporary Pagan spirituality in the British Unitarian community.<ref>[http://www.ukunitarians.org.uk/earthspirit/background.htm UESN Background] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120526165316/http://www.ukunitarians.org.uk/earthspirit/background.htm |date=May 26, 2012 }}, UESN official web site</ref>
