'''Dafydd Emlyn''' was a 17th century [[Welsh people|Welsh]] poet and [[Clergy|cleric]]. It is thought he may have been from the [[Teifi Valley]]. A number of his works are known to survive, some of which are written in his own hand.
<ref>{{cite web|title=Dafydd Emlyn|url=http://yba.llgc.org.uk/en/s-DAFY-EML-1603.html|website=Dictionary of Welsh Biography|publisher=National Library of Wales|last=Williams|first=Griffith John|accessdate=22 November 2016}}</ref>

