[[File:Eglwys Gadeiriol Llanelwy - St Asaph Cathedral.jpg|thumb|St Asaph Cathedral]]
'''Dafydd ab Ieuan ab Iorwerth'''{{Pronunciation needed}}<!-- as IPA --> (died in or before 1503)<ref>{{Cite ODNB |first=David H. |last=Williams |year=2005 |title=Dafydd ab Ieuan ab Iorwerth (d. in or before 1503), abbot of Valle Crucis and bishop of St Asaph |url=http://www.oxforddnb.com/view/article/93721 |doi=10.1093/ref:odnb/93721 }}</ref> was [[Bishop of St Asaph]] from 1500 to 1503.

His family was from the [[Trefor]] area of [[Gwynedd]], and descendants of Tudur ap Rhys Sais.

Prior to his appointment he was [[Abbot]] of [[Valle Crucis Abbey|Valle Crucis]]. He provided hospitality to, and was liberal patron of the bards, as acknowledged by [[Gutun Owain]] and [[Guto'r Glyn]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Dafydd ap Iorwerth|url=http://yba.llgc.org.uk/en/s-DAFY-API-1503.html|website=Dictionary of Welsh Biography|publisher=National Library of Wales|accessdate=27 September 2016}}</ref>

