'''Qari Ghulam Rasool''' (1935–2014) was a great Qari and an Islamic scholar of his time who was from [[Pakistan]].<ref name="awamipol">{{cite web|url=http://www.awamipolitics.com/qari-ghulam-rasool-dies-in-lahore-15431.html|title=Qari Ghulam Rasool Dies in Lahore|accessdate=2017-06-14}}</ref> He was born in 1935 in [[Lahore]]. He received education from famous seminary [[Darsgah Hizbul Ehnaf]]. He learned Qirat from [[Qari Abdul Malik]] and later on became famous across the globe due to God-gifted qualities. He was awarded numerous awards besides a presidential award.<ref name="awamipol" /> He had recited the Quran at PTV and [[Radio Pakistan]] for more than 50 years.<ref name="awamipol" />
He also taught at [[Jamia Nizamia]] and later on established his own five madaris. He was a close friend of [[Shah Ahmad Noorani]] and [[Abdul Sattar Khan Niazi]].
He died on 9 March 2014.<ref>http://nation.com.pk/lahore/10-Mar-2014/qari-ghulam-rasool-passes-away</ref>
